## Common Pitfalls

### Follow-for-Follow and Engagement Pods

Wrong: Join engagement pods or do follow-for-follow exchanges to inflate follower count and engagement metrics artificially.

Right: Build a genuine audience through valuable content and authentic engagement. Fake engagement signals confuse algorithms and attract the wrong audience. Quality followers who actually care about your content are the only ones that matter.

### Giveaway-Driven Growth

Wrong: Run "follow + tag 3 friends to win" giveaways as the primary growth strategy, attracting followers who unfollow the moment the giveaway ends.

Right: If using giveaways, tie them to genuine brand engagement (share your story, create content with product, answer a meaningful question). Accept that a portion of giveaway followers will churn and plan accordingly.

### Ignoring Existing Followers to Chase New Ones

Wrong: Obsess over acquisition metrics while neglecting the community that already follows you. Never respond to comments, never acknowledge loyal followers.

Right: Retention is cheaper than acquisition. A follower who stays engaged for a year is worth more than ten followers who leave after a week. Prioritize community health alongside growth metrics.
